From 0000000000000000000000000000000000000000 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: SuperKali <hello@superkali.me>
Date: Thu, 2 Jul 2026 22:05:20 +0200
Subject: drm/msm/dp: stop enabling the PLL unlocked interrupt

DP_INTR_PLL_UNLOCKED is enabled as part of DP_INTERRUPT_STATUS1 but
no isr handles it: the events land in the AUX isr, which logs the
misleading "Unexpected DP AUX IRQ 0x01000000 when not busy" for
every PLL unlock during link bring-up and teardown. Drop the bit
from the group so the interrupt is never armed.

Signed-off-by: SuperKali <hello@superkali.me>
---
 drivers/gpu/drm/msm/dp/dp_ctrl.c | 2 +-
 1 file changed, 1 insertion(+), 1 deletion(-)

diff --git a/drivers/gpu/drm/msm/dp/dp_ctrl.c b/drivers/gpu/drm/msm/dp/dp_ctrl.c
index 111111111111..222222222222 100644
--- a/drivers/gpu/drm/msm/dp/dp_ctrl.c
+++ b/drivers/gpu/drm/msm/dp/dp_ctrl.c
@@ -43,7 +43,7 @@
 	DP_INTR_WRONG_ADDR | DP_INTR_TIMEOUT | \
 	DP_INTR_NACK_DEFER | DP_INTR_WRONG_DATA_CNT | \
 	DP_INTR_I2C_NACK | DP_INTR_I2C_DEFER | \
-	DP_INTR_PLL_UNLOCKED | DP_INTR_AUX_ERROR)
+	DP_INTR_AUX_ERROR)
 
 #define DP_INTERRUPT_STATUS1_ACK \
 	(DP_INTERRUPT_STATUS1 << DP_INTERRUPT_STATUS_ACK_SHIFT)
-- 
Armbian

